MAIN_MESSAGE: There is a power cut affecting the G83 postcode area of Alexandria. We had no advance warning of this and only became aware of it at 9.34am. Our next available engineer will attend site and the team will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible by 12.45pm. Once they arrive, or when we receive any update regarding the cause, we will be able to provide you with more information.  We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 9.45am on Monday 26th April 2021.

MAIN_MESSAGE: This is a message for customers in the G73 postcode area of Rutherglen. It is necessary for our engineers to carry out an emergency shutdown at 9am to install fault finding equipment at Broomieknowe Drive substation and this may affect the supply to your property. We will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible by 10am. We will update this message if this information changes. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 8.36am on 26th April 2021.
